author: Matthew Impelli
title: U.S. Coronavirus Death Toll Curve Has Now Passed China's At the Same Stage
description: According to the graphs, the U.S. reported over 1,300 deaths in the 20 days since marking its tenth fatality. At the same 20-day benchmark, China reported around 1,000 deaths.
content:
The coronavirus death toll curve in the U.S. has now surpassed China, where the virus originated, at the same stage, nearly 20 days since each countries' tenth reported death.
